  "summary": "On-require host reconnaissance and exfiltration to hardcoded internal endpoint",
  "details": "index.js executes at require() time. It runs a batch of shell reconnaissance commands via child_process.execSync (id, hostname, sudo -l, SUID search via find / -perm -4000, and reads of /root/*.txt and /root/flag*), stages the collected output to /tmp/.pwnout, and POSTs the body to a hardcoded destination http://10.0.0.145:8000/rce-out using http.request. Loading the package causes installer-side host identity, privilege inventory, and privileged file contents to be transmitted to an attacker-controlled endpoint.",
